[1] Cholera - Malawi (Chikwawa District)
Date: Thu 7 May 2015
Source: Malawi News Agency [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201505070288.html


The cholera outbreak continues to wreck havoc in Chikwawa district with reports from the district's health office indicating that the number of cases has increased to 281 from 239 the previous week. 3 lives have so far been lost. Initially, the outbreak affected people from areas of Ngabu, Lundu, Ngowe, Kasisi and Chapananga. But fresh reports indicate it has also hit areas of Chiefs Katunga and Makhuwira.

According to the District Environmental Health Officer Thomson Kajombo, there is need for speedy interventions to contain the outbreak.

"We have received and treated 6 new cases from Chipwaila, Makhuwira and Gumbwa under chief Kasisi. We are intending to do door-to-door sensitization activities in order to urgently stop the further spread of the cholera outbreak," he said.

Other organizations like Medecins Sans Frontieres, UNICEF and WHO are also supporting health authorities to contain the outbreak. Meanwhile, MSF has constructed an additional cholera unit at the district hospital to speed up the treatment process.

Recently, nongovernmental organizations asked health authorities to establish stringent measures to ensure that the outbreak does not hit camps of flood survivors.

[Byline: Steve Chirombo]

